      "lotl": {
        "label": "What's Going On With the Commanders",
        "body": "The draft smoke thickens around Washington, where a 5-12 stumble left them third in the NFC East - six games back, but armed with the <strong>14th overall pick</strong> and a war chest of needs from the trenches to the secondary. GM Adam Peters, fresh off inking edge rusher Dante Fowler Jr. in free agency, eyes a roster rebuild that screams opportunism; their linebackers leak like a sieve, corners invite YAC feasts, and the D-line craves depth beyond Jonathan Allen's twilight. Mock drafts swirl with trade-down buzz - <strong>Washington shopping that top-15 slot for a second-round sweetener, zeroing in on NC State's lockdown corner Mansoor Delane</strong> while whispers of Miami's explosive Rueben Bain Jr. tempt a pass-rush spike. QB Jayden Daniels' sophomore leap hinges on protection, yet Peters plays coy, dodging trade-up fever for volume picks to stock Dan Quinn's defense. No splashy free-agent regrets linger; it's all chess now. <strong>With the draft clock ticking to late April, watch if they flip the script Thursday - Delane's length or Bain's bend could redefine this rebuild overnight.</strong>",
        "updated": "Updated April 20, 2026"
